 A
five-year-old child died in a house fire in Lenasia on Monday morning, the City
of Johannesburg's Emergency Management Services (EMS) say. Firefighters
were called to the scene on Albatross Street around 08:00 and found a
double-storey house on fire, EMS spokesperson Nana Radebe said. "Unfortunately,
a five-year-old died from smoke inhalation," she said. Fire at a house in Fire on Albatross Street Lenasia. 5-year-old died. pic.twitter.com/MLKoL2VkSo  Radebe
added that it had taken about an hour to extinguish the fire. The cause
of the fire is still unclear and fire safety officers were on scene conducting
preliminary investigations. SOURCE:
